                            <comment id="13004770" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 20:09:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m actually not sure how this could help &amp;#8211; dfile.close() already un-references the buffer, so there&apos;s no need to set dfile itself to be null.  Also, the file pointer changes as we read through the file, so changing bytescomplete to init-once is broken. (This is what nodetool compactionstats uses.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My guess is that the second time around you just got lucky and index build was able to keep up w/ streaming enough to avoid OOMing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But there is a bug here with the file/buffer handling &amp;#8211; we should lazy-init this once we&apos;re ready to build the index, rather than when we enqueue the task.  Patch attached w/ this approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004772" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2011 20:14:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 overcomplicated the problem.  v3 attached w/o extra Builder fields.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
